const overview = `The Langtang Valley Trek is often described as the "Valley of Glaciers" and serves as the closest major Himalayan trekking region to Kathmandu. Despite its proximity to the capital, it remains surprisingly wild and less commercialized than the Everest or Annapurna routes. The journey begins in the lush forests of Langtang National Park—home to the elusive Red Panda—and climbs steadily into vast alpine meadows surrounded by snow-capped giants like Langtang Lirung (7,227m).

The region is culturally distinct, inhabited primarily by the Tamang people whose heritage is deeply rooted in Tibetan Buddhism. As you trek past mani walls and prayer wheels, you witness a community known for its resilience and hospitality, particularly following the recovery from the 2015 earthquake. The trail culminates at Kyanjin Gompa, a spiritual center surrounded by peaks, offering a perfect blend of moderate adventure, stunning biodiversity, and rich culture.`;
